<title>SWITZERLAND: Swiss short-time work rose in January.</title>
<headline>Swiss short-time work rose in January.</headline>
<dateline>BERNE</dateline>
<text>
<p>The number of people affected by short-time work in Switzerland rose to 14,948 in January 1997, an increase of 4,216, or 39.3 percent, from December 1996, the Federal Office for Industry and Trade said.</p>
<p>The number of work hours lost to short-time working increased by 65.1 percent to 931,388. In January 1996 there were 801,606 hours lost. -- Zurich Editorial +41 1 631 7340</p>
